HEADWORD: Growler
<hw>Growl"er</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>One who
growls.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>The large-mouthed black
bass.</def> <mark>[Local]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>A four-wheeled cab.</def> <mark>[Slang,
Eng.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Growlingly</ent>⟦br⟧
